      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|><|channel>thought\n<channel|><|channel>thought\n<channel|><|channel>thought\n<channel|>Wait, hold on. If you're that ready to sign, why the rush to sign at *this* specific price? Usually, when companies are in a \"procurement emergency\" like you're implying, they're willing to pay a premium for immediate delivery. If you're that desperate for the supply, shouldn't you be more concerned about the shipping timeline than just locking in the rate? Give me one good reason why I should prioritize your paperwork over other buyers who are willing to pay more for the same urgency.",
