      "content": "That sounds like a sales pitch, not a procurement strategy. You're telling me you're ready to sign *right now* to lock in the price, but then you're talking about \"partnership value\" and \"future production runs.\" \n\nIf your factory is actually facing an imminent shortage like you implied, every minute you spend debating \"partnership value\" with me is a minute you're closer to a line shutdown. If you're truly in an urgent situation, you wouldn't be negotiating the philosophy of the deal—you'd just be signing the contract to ensure the steel arrives. Are you actually facing a critical supply gap, or is this just a tactic to get this specific rate?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
